You turn on your heel and walk away, keeping your expression carefully neutral. Behind you, Ms. Greene exhales sharply—a clipped, exasperated scoff, just loud enough to be heard but not quite enough to be addressed directly. You catch a few unintelligible words muttered under her breath, undoubtedly not a compliment.

You don’t bother looking back. Let her think what she wants.

Now, the only question is: Where to next?
